# AI Search Audit Design Rule

Source of truth:

1. docs/DESIGN_SYSTEM.md
2. docs/homepage-reference.png

If there is any conflict, DESIGN_SYSTEM.md wins.

Requirements:

- Read docs/DESIGN_SYSTEM.md before making any UI decision.
- Review docs/homepage-reference.png before changing layouts or components.
- Do not introduce new colors.
- Do not introduce new typography scales.
- Do not introduce new spacing systems.
- Do not introduce new shadows.
- Do not introduce new border radius values.
- Do not introduce new component styles.
- Do not redesign approved UI.
- Build reusable components.
- Maintain consistency across all pages.
- Reuse existing components whenever possible.
- If a design change is required, update docs/DESIGN_SYSTEM.md first.

For every UI task:

1. Review docs/DESIGN_SYSTEM.md
2. Review docs/homepage-reference.png
3. Check for an existing reusable component before creating a new one
4. Implement the change
5. Keep the design system consistent

Never make design assumptions that are not defined in the design system.